    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Dayton</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 413.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 5, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Immediately upon the reception of your
                            despatch, No. 451, I called the attention of Mr. Drouyn de l’Huys to the
                            fact of the imprisonment of J. H. Mansfield, consul at Tobasco, and
                            asked the reasons therefor. He said that he was not at all in possession
                            of the facts, nor did he know the grounds of his imprisonment, but he
                            would make a memorandum of the case, and give me the necessary
                            information at an early day.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. L. DAYTON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
